\section{Rendering hints for blocked steps}

Hints are part of the student-facing tutorial text too.  Rendering them
through the same Markdown path keeps inline commands looking consistent
between the pre-step prompt and the follow-up guidance after a failed
step.

<<functions>>=
def render_hint(console: Console, hint: str) -> None:
    """Render a step hint as Markdown."""

    console.print()
    console.print("Hint", style="bold")
    console.print(Markdown(hint))
    console.print()
@

